FBIS4-57804 "drlat101_m_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 Brazil Lula's Use of Union Van Seen as Electoral Violation Lula's Use of Union Van Seen as Electoral Violation PY2505021194 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 24 May 94 p 1 PY2505021194 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO Portuguese BFN [Text] One day after the Sole Workers Center [CUT] decided in its national congress that it can neither support nor aid the Workers Party [PT], PT presidential candidate Luis Inacio Lula da Silva campaigned on 23 May outside factories in the Sao Paulo ABC region from a loudspeaker-equipped van owned by the CUT-affiliated metalworkers union. On 23 May, Lula, who said earlier he is against CUT support, stated it is up to the workers to decide who should use the van. In the opinion of electoral specialist Antonio Carlos Mendes, Lula violated electoral laws.
